## New findings (if any)
[MEDIUM] [scope_classifier_llm.py:393](</C:/POLARIS/src/polaris_graph/audit_ir/scope_classifier_llm.py:393>) — `llm_out.verdict` is normalized with `.lower().strip()` before any type check. A malformed `LLMVerdict(verdict=None, ...)` raises raw `AttributeError` instead of `LLMScopeClassifierError`, so bad LLM output can escape the adapter contract and bubble through the phase-1 gate as an unexpected hard failure.

[MEDIUM] [scope_classifier_llm.py:401](</C:/POLARIS/src/polaris_graph/audit_ir/scope_classifier_llm.py:401>) — `confidence` validation accepts `bool` because `bool` is a subclass of `int`. A backend returning `confidence=True` is silently adapted as `1.0`, which can turn malformed LLM output into a high-confidence `IN_SCOPE` result instead of rejecting it.

## Final word
